WHEREAS, the organization continues to advocate for national media
acknowledgment of coastal restoration efforts, infrastructure needs, and other issues that are
vital to the rebuilding of wetlands in Louisiana and along the Gulf Coast; and
WHEREAS, Women of the Storm is most deserving of the highest recognition for
its unrelenting pursuit of the restoration of the diverse communities along the Gulf Coast.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Women of the Storm on the occasion of its
twentieth anniversary and does hereby extend enduring appreciation for its members'
contributions to the communities along the Gulf Coast.
